==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Terpenylic
<hw>Ter`pe*nyl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Terpene</ets> + <ets>-yl</ets> + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid,
<chform>C8H12O4</chform> (called also <xex>terpentic acid</xex>),
homologous with terebic acid, and obtained as a white crystalline
substance by the oxidation of oil of turpentine with chromic
acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terpilene</ent>⟦br⟧
